Ginger Frozen Yogurt
  --America's Test Kitchen

1 qt whole milk yogurt
1 tsp unflavored powdered gelatin
1 tbsp fresh grated ginger
1 tsp powdered ginger
3/4 c sugar
1/4 c lyle's golden syrup (measurement may be off)
1/8 tsp salt

Drain yogurt - pour into 3 layers cheesecloth in a mesh strainer over a bowl, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 3 hrs up to overnight. Pour off 3/4 c of the drained whey, keep 1/2 c whey. Pour gelatin into whey, let sit for 5 min. Microwave for 30 sec. to disolve. Add gingers to whey and stir; let sit for 5 min. Pour yogurt into bowl, pour whey mixture through a fine mesh strainer (to get rid of fresh bits) into same bowl, press to get all the flavor out. Add sugar, salt, and syrup, whisk to combine until sugar is completely dissolved. Cover with plastic and put in refrigerator until it gets to ~40F. Churn as specified by manufacturer's instructions for ice cream maker. Looking for 21F (25-35 min). Put in freezer for at least 2 hrs.
